The paper discusses the design and implementation of a distributed database system, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses load-balancing and resource utilization, which are important topics in Database Systems (cs.DB) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper mentions the reduction of manual administration, which is a topic in Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the autonomic nature of the system, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
